Sisa Canca, News24SA Police. (Duncan Alfreds, News24, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg -&nbsp;Three men disguised as police officers stole an undisclosed amount of money in a cash-in-transit heist on the N4 near Pretoria North on Thursday, police said.Three security guards in an SBV van were on their way from Rustenburg to Pretoria in the early hours when they heard a loud bang and stopped, Lieutenant&nbsp;Kay Makhubela said.The guards opened the door and three men in police uniform approached them, disarmed them and took the money they were transporting.They fled in a white car with police markings. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.